--- In nbwrpg@yahoogroups.com, EmprzAnastazia@a... wrote:
> In a message dated 5/10/03 10:52:35 PM Central Daylight Time, 
> airly2002@h... writes:
> 
> 
> > "I'll be fine"said Blackstorm by com link.
> > 
> > 
> 
> "Fine is not what bothers me." Pausing a moment. "If the others 
know of this 
> place, or worse... DON'T know of this place & followed or tracked 
us... it's 
> guaranteed that they will eventually show. This is no place for a 
battle. Nor 
> for wandering bots." Another pause. "I've set the defenses here at 
full 
> around the perimeter. You are my only contact now with the other 
predacons, 
> Blackstorm. Return to base, inform them that I shall be.. detained 
for a 
> time. I shall return & report back soon. If you so desire, return 
to the 
> outer perimeter as well. But I would prefer not. It may attract 
attention. & 
> that is the LAST thing I want to do." 
> 
> Within her, she was so torn. She ached to return to the Predacon 
base. 
> Curious to know of Hydras. She had to admit it, but she would 
never show it. 
> Unless it was around him, privately.. no one else watching or 
nearby. 
> Emotions were not something to have, specially for a Decepticon 
warrior. 
> 
> But as her optics went to the frozen limp form of the original 
Megatron... 
> the ache was worse.
